{"article_id":"HFE8JNUsnyRH1nsM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"BREAKING THIS MORNING -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"SESSIONS TAPPED AS ATTORNEY GENERAL :","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"President-elect Donald Trump has tapped Alabama Sen. Jeff Sessions to be his attorney general ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"according to transition official Sean Spicer .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"As Trump 's first Senate supporter and close adviser during the campaign , the four-term Republican senator effectively had his pick of Cabinet posts in the new administration .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Sessions was bandied about for defense secretary or secretary of homeland security ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"but ultimately his focus in the Senate on illegal immigration","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"- and hard-line views","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that align with Trump ' s -","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"led him to be selected to lead the Justice Department .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"But Sessions ' confirmation is likely to be a fight ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"even though he ' s a senator ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"and it could turn ugly .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"His critics are expected to seize on his failed confirmation three decades ago ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"when the Judiciary Committee rejected his nomination over accusations","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"he had called the NAACP \" un-American \"","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and addressed a black lawyer as \" boy . \"","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"FLYNN IS IN -","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"TRUMP OFFERS NATIONAL SECURITY POST ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"our colleague Bryan Bender has more on the former defense intelligence chief here :","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"\" President-elect Donald Trump has tapped retired Lt. Gen. Mike Flynn , one of his top confidants , to be White House national security adviser ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"which would elevate the controversial surrogate","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"to be the chief arbiter of virtually every major defense and foreign policy decision . `` The choice of Flynn ,","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"who was known as a skilled , if combative intelligence officer during his 33-year career","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"but was forced out as head of the Defense Intelligence Agency in 2014 ,","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"signals the president-elect ' s intention","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"to wage an aggressive war on terrorism","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"- possibly without the diplomatic and cultural sensitivities","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"that have been the hallmark of President Barack Obama ' s approach ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"which Flynn has repeatedly criticized . \"","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"Flynn ' s appointment was confirmed to by a source close to the Trump transition on Thursday night ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"though it was not clear whether Flynn has responded .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"In the past , Flynn , 58 , has argued","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"that ' Islam is a political ideology , ' one","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"that in his view ' the American Founding Fathers wanted nothing to do with. '","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"His hardline views","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"- as well as laudatory statements about Russia -","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"have made him a lightning rod ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"as did his strident attacks on Hillary Clinton during the campaign ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"including leading chants at Trump rallies of ' Lock her up . ' \"","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"POMPEO HEADED TO CIA :","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Trump is making it a hat trick of appointments","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"by naming Rep. Mike Pompeo","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"( R-Kan. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"who has served on the House Intelligence Committee as well as the Benghazi Select Committee ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"as CIA director .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Trump will announce all three picks today ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"our colleague Kyle Cheney reports .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"- DEMOCRATS SOUND OFF :","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"The House Intelligence Committee 's top Democrat on Thursday called Flynn a bad choice ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"questioning the retired general 's temperament and cozy relationship with Russia .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"\" I ' d like to see someone with very sober judgment with a temperament","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"that complements rather than accentuates the eccentricities of the incoming president , \"","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"Rep. Adam Schiff of California said at the DefenseOne Summit .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"The top Democrat on the Senate Armed Services Committee , Sen. Jack Reed of Rhode Island , had a more complementary view ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"praising the military service of Flynn , a Rhode Island native ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"while saying","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"he had \" concerns about some of the statements","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"he made in the heat of the campaign . ''","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"- CONGRESS AND THE NSC :","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Of course , it doesn ' t matter much what Congress thinks :","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"The national security adviser does n't require confirmation .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Ironically , however , Republicans on the House and Senate Armed Services Committees have included provisions in the defense authorization bills","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to curb the NSC with caps on staff and a possible Senate confirmation requirement","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"- measures","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"taken in response to President Barack Obama ' s National Security Council .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"We ' ll see","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"if they make the final version of the bill .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"HAPPENING TODAY -","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"HALIFAX SECURITY FORUM :","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"The annual Halifax International Security Forum kicks off today in one of Morning D ' s favorite parts of Canada .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Among the bold-faced names","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"headed north for the meetings","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"that runs through the weekend :","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"Sens . McCain , Jeanne Shaheen","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"( D-N.H. ) ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Chris Coons","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"( D-Del . )","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"and John Barrasso","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"( R-Wyo . ) ,","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"retired Gen. John Allen and James Baker , director of the Pentagon ' s Office of Net Assessment .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"The full schedule is here .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"THE FIRST WEEK OF THE LAME DUCK IS DONE","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"WHERE THINGS STAND :","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Congress left town Thursday for a weeklong Thanksgiving break ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"when they return ,","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"the spending bill and National Defense Authorization Act will be at the top of the agenda .","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"But","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"while the NDAA appears poised for passage in December ,","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"Congress is planning to pass a continuing spending resolution through the end of March ,","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"giving the new Trump administration a chance","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"to make its mark on the fiscal 2017 spending process .","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"More on the spending situation here :","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"\" Capitol Hill Republicans and the incoming Trump administration are nearing agreement on a plan","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"to fund the government at current levels through March 31 ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"House Speaker Paul Ryan","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"( R-Wis. )","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"told lawmakers during a closed-door meeting Thursday .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"\" The short-term patch is aimed at giving Trump a say in next year 's funding priorities","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"and preventing President Barack Obama from putting his mark on a massive spending deal .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"... House Republicans have little interest","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"in negotiating with a lame-duck Obama .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Punting to early next year ,","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"when Trump will be in the White House with a GOP Congress ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"will give the right more leverage","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"to get its spending priorities and pet policy riders into law . \" -","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"TWO SCHOOLS OF THOUGHT ON DEFENSE :","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Senate Armed Services Chairman John McCain","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"( R-Ariz. )","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"was livid over the planned CR .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"He gave a floor speech Thursday","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"blasting congressional leaders","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"for failing to pass a defense appropriations bill","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"and relying on a CR","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"that \" would lock our military into last year ' s budget and last year ' s priorities. \"","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"Afterward ,","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"he told Military Times","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"readiness will suffer","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"\" if these idiots say","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"they want to go through with a continuing resolution . \"","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"Rep. Mike Turner","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"( R-Ohio ) ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"who has been a leader","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"pushing for more defense spending ,","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"had a more positive view .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"\" When we come back in March ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"the president can ask us to increase the number even more","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"and hopefully we can take care of some of the shortfalls , \"","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"he told Morning D .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"- THE WAR SUPPLEMENTAL STILL COULD MOVE IN THE LAME DUCK :","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"The Obama administration has also requested an additional $ 11.6 billion in war funding for Afghanistan and Iraq .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"House Appropriations Chairman Hal Rogers said","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"he and his colleagues would try to deliver those funds in the lame-duck session ,","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"reports our colleague Ben Weyl .","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"`` That obviously is terribly important , ''","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"he told reporters .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"`` We want to be sure","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"that our military has adequate resources during this interim period . ''","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"NDAA WATCH -","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"MORE PROGRESS","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"AS FINAL BILL IS WITHIN REACH ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"after controversial policy riders were dropped as part of the emerging deal on the defense policy bill ,","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"we report with Connor O ' Brien :","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"\" House and Senate negotiators","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"putting the finishing touches on the new defense policy bill","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"are ditching the controversial riders","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"that could draw a presidential veto .","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"The final version of the National Defense Authorization Act will not include provisions","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"dealing with the greater sage grouse or workplace protections","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"based on sexual orientation ,","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"according to sources familiar with the negotiations .","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"\" The provisions were two of the major sticking points between the House and Senate versions of the bill","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"and were part of the reason","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"Armed Services leaders were unable to strike an accord in September . ...","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"Committee aides and leaders cautioned","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"that nothing was officially finalized","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"until the entire bill was completed .","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"But one House Armed Services member said","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"they ' ve been told","depth":15},{"id":161,"text":"negotiations on issues","depth":17},{"id":162,"text":"where the two chambers differed","depth":17},{"id":163,"text":"are all wrapped up .","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"' It ' s done , '","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"the lawmaker said .","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"' There ' s no more negotiations , even on the small stuff . ' \"","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"- WHEN WILL THE FINAL BILL BE RELEASED ?","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"House and Senate leaders have no reason","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"to wrap up negotiations","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"and put out the conference report","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"until Congress returns after Thanksgiving ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"not to mention","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"they need to collect signatures from lawmakers","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"who have left town .","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"But it ' s a likely item for Congress to take up that first week back .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"THE TRUMP TRANSITION -","depth":4},{"id":177,"text":"ADD ANOTHER NAME TO THE RUMOR MILL ...","depth":5},{"id":178,"text":"PETRAEUS ,","depth":6},{"id":179,"text":"as The Guardian added his name to the now long list of secretary of state candidates :","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"\" David Petraeus","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"- the former US army general and CIA director","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"who was prosecuted for mishandling classified information -","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"has entered the race","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"to become Donald Trump ' s secretary of state ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"diplomatic sources said on Thursday . \"","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"- ABE MEETS TRUMP ,","depth":6},{"id":187,"text":"via The Associated Press ' Michael Astor :","depth":6},{"id":188,"text":"\" Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe said","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"he believes","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"Donald Trump is a leader","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"in whom he can have great confidence","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"after meeting with the president-elect Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"Abe ,","depth":9},{"id":194,"text":"who became the first world leader","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"to meet with Trump since his election ,","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"was seeking reassurances over the future of U.S.-Japan security and trade relations .","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"He described the meeting as ' really , really cordial '","depth":7},{"id":198,"text":"but offered few details of their discussion . \"","depth":7},{"id":199,"text":"- OTHERS","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"WHO MET WITH TRUMP THURSDAY :","depth":8},{"id":201,"text":"Retired Gen. Jack Keane and NSA Director and Cyber Command chief Adm. Mike Rogers .","depth":7},{"id":202,"text":"- WE HAVE CONTACT :","depth":7},{"id":203,"text":"The Trump transition team called the Pentagon on Thursday","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"to arrange initial briefings ,","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"Defense Department press secretary Peter Cook said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":206,"text":"The first briefings are expected to take place today ,","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"Cook said ,","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"and the transition team told reporters","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"it ' ll be releasing a list of names on the \" landing team \"","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"coordinating with the Pentagon officials .","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"DNI SHAKE-UP","depth":7},{"id":212,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"CLAPPER SUBMITS HIS RESIGNATION ,","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"our colleagues Martin Matishak and Bryan Bender have more here :","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"\" Director of National Intelligence James Clapper said Thursday","depth":15},{"id":216,"text":"that he has submitted his resignation to President Barack Obama","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"and will not stay on past the transition to Donald Trump .","depth":14},{"id":218,"text":"Clapper offered the news during his opening statement in a rare open hearing of the House Intelligence Committee","depth":14},{"id":219,"text":"after the panel 's ranking Democrat , Adam Schiff of California , said","depth":15},{"id":220,"text":"he had heard rumors","depth":16},{"id":221,"text":"that the spy chief might stay on into the Trump administration .","depth":16},{"id":222,"text":"\" That 's not going to happen ,","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"Clapper said .","depth":13},{"id":224,"text":"' I submitted my letter of resignation last night ,","depth":14},{"id":225,"text":"which felt pretty good , '","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":227,"text":"' I got 64 days left ,","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"and I think","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"I 'd have a hard time with my wife anything past that. ' ...","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"The most controversial aspect of Clapper 's tenure may have been his statement to a Senate panel in 2013","depth":12},{"id":231,"text":"that U.S. spy agencies were not collecting data on American citizens","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"- a claim","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"later contradicted by information","depth":13},{"id":234,"text":"leaked by National Security Agency contractor Edward Snowden . \"","depth":13},{"id":235,"text":"- The Nusra Front is trying to rebrand","depth":8},{"id":236,"text":"as one of its alleged leaders is placed on the terrorist watch list :","depth":8},{"id":237,"text":"The New York Times -","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"Iraqis","depth":11},{"id":239,"text":"trapped in Mosul","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"call into an anti-Islamic State radio program","depth":11},{"id":241,"text":"to talk about their life under the regime :","depth":11},{"id":242,"text":"The Washington Post -","depth":10},{"id":243,"text":"Britain is set to buy as many as 26 predator drones for up to $ 1 billion :","depth":11},{"id":244,"text":"The Washington Post -","depth":11},{"id":245,"text":"One in four service members is concerned about life under a Trump presidency ,","depth":12},{"id":246,"text":"according to a new poll :","depth":12},{"id":247,"text":"Military Times -","depth":11},{"id":248,"text":"The International Atomic Energy Agency warns Iran to stick to the terms of the nuclear deal","depth":13},{"id":249,"text":"after the country stockpiles slightly more than the allowed amount of heavy water :","depth":13},{"id":250,"text":"The Wall Street Journal -","depth":12},{"id":251,"text":"Iraqi forces struggle to distinguish Islamic State fighters from ally or civilian in Mosul :","depth":14},{"id":252,"text":"Reuters -","depth":14},{"id":253,"text":"The House votes to bar sales of commercial aircraft to Iran :","depth":14},{"id":254,"text":"Reuters -","depth":15},{"id":255,"text":"Army Secretary Eric Fanning says","depth":16},{"id":256,"text":"the Army still struggles to buy commercial products :","depth":16},{"id":257,"text":"Defense News -","depth":14},{"id":258,"text":"How the military has had to shift from \" secret wars \" to \" low visibility \" ones :","depth":14},{"id":259,"text":"Defense One -","depth":15},{"id":260,"text":"Chief Master Sgt . Kaleth Wright is named the 18th chief master sergeant of the Air Force :","depth":15},{"id":261,"text":"Stars and Stripes -","depth":15},{"id":262,"text":"A Munich court rejects a U.S. Army deserter ' s request for asylum :","depth":18},{"id":263,"text":"The Associated Press -","depth":18},{"id":264,"text":"HillVets is pushing for more veterans to work as congressional staff :","depth":17},{"id":265,"text":"Military Times -","depth":18},{"id":266,"text":"Navy football is one win away from its first conference championship game ever :","depth":18},{"id":267,"text":"The Washington Post -","depth":19},{"id":268,"text":"The White House is desperately looking for replacement Air Force Ones :","depth":19},{"id":269,"text":"Military.com -","depth":19},{"id":270,"text":"Marines successfully 3D print a replacement part in field conditions :","depth":20},{"id":271,"text":"Marines Times","depth":20}],"relations":[{"parent":543,"left":0,"right":542,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":542,"left":446,"right":541,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":446,"left":287,"right":445,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":287,"left":1,"right":286,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":279,"right":285,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":274,"right":278,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":274,"left":273,"right":4,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":5,"right":277,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":276,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":276,"left":6,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":281,"right":284,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":280,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"adversative","nucleari